properties.Name: OrganizationCriteriaType
properties.Description:
Organization Criteria Type is a means of classifying, grouping or categorizing specific Organization Criteria at a higher level for analysis and presentation.

Organization Criteria are a means to identify what 'positions' or 'organizational responsibilities' an individual has.   

An organization can be defined for both professional organizations ('Employment') or the family organization ("Housewife")

The Organization Criteria Type is the larger classification to which the Organization Criteria belongs.

The following are examples:

Organization Criteria:   "Housewife"
Organization Criteria Type:  "Family"

Organization Criteria:   "Manager"
Organization Criteria Type:  "Employment"

Organization Criteria:  "Manufacturing Supervisor"
Organization Criteria Type:  "Job Function"

Organization Criteria:  "Manager"
Organization Criteria Type:  "Job Title"

Organization Criteria:  "Accounting Clerical"
Organization Criteria Type:  "Clerical"

Each organization will identify, define and track a specific set of Organization Criteria to gather information about, define consumers and make decisions.

Columns.Name: OrganizationCriteriaTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Organization Criteria Type.

Columns.Name: OrganizationCriteriaTypeName
Columns.Description: The name of the Organization Criteria Type.

Columns.Name: OrganizationCriteriaTypeDescription
Columns.Description: The description of the Organization Criteria Type.
